280	  /**
281	   * Optional channel runtime helpers for external channel plugins.
282	   *
283	   * This field provides access to advanced Plugin SDK features that are
284	   * available to external plugins but not to built-in channels (which can
285	   * directly import internal modules).
286	   *
287	   * ## Available Features
288	   *
289	   * - **reply**: AI response dispatching, formatting, and delivery
290	   * - **routing**: Agent route resolution and matching
291	   * - **text**: Text chunking, markdown processing, and control command detection
292	   * - **session**: Session management and metadata tracking
293	   * - **media**: Remote media fetching and buffer saving
294	   * - **commands**: Command authorization and control command handling
295	   * - **groups**: Group policy resolution and mention requirements
296	   * - **pairing**: Channel pairing and allow-from management
297	   *
298	   * ## Use Cases
299	   *
300	   * External channel plugins (e.g., email, SMS, custom integrations) that need:
301	   * - AI-powered response generation and delivery
302	   * - Advanced text processing and formatting
303	   * - Session tracking and management
304	   * - Agent routing and policy resolution
305	   *
306	   * ## Example
307	   *
308	   * ```typescript
309	   * const emailGatewayAdapter: ChannelGatewayAdapter<EmailAccount> = {
310	   *   startAccount: async (ctx) => {
311	   *     // Check availability (for backward compatibility)
312	   *     if (!ctx.channelRuntime) {
313	   *       ctx.log?.warn?.("channelRuntime not available - skipping AI features");
314	   *       return;
315	   *     }
316	   *
317	   *     // Use AI dispatch
318	   *     await ctx.channelRuntime.reply.dispatchReplyWithBufferedBlockDispatcher({
319	   *       ctx: { ... },
320	   *       cfg: ctx.cfg,
321	   *       dispatcherOptions: {
322	   *         deliver: async (payload) => {
323	   *           // Send reply via email
324	   *         },
325	   *       },
326	   *     });
327	   *   },
328	   * };
329	   * ```
330	   *
331	   * ## Backward Compatibility
332	   *
333	   * - This field is **optional** - channels that don't need it can ignore it
334	   * - Built-in channels (slack, discord, etc.) typically don't use this field
335	   *   because they can directly import internal modules
336	   * - External plugins should check for undefined before using
337	   *
338	   * @since Plugin SDK 2026.2.19
339	   * @see {@link https://docs.openclaw.ai/plugins/developing-plugins | Plugin SDK documentation}
340	   */
341	  channelRuntime?: PluginRuntime["channel"];
342	};
